de.bioforscher.singa.structure.model.oak

Interface Exchangeable<FamilyType extends StructuralFamily>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AminoAcid, LeafSubstructure<FamilyType>, Ligand, Nucleotide
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MmtfAminoAcid, MmtfLeafSubstructure, MmtfLigand, MmtfNucleotide, OakAminoAcid, OakLeafSubstructure, OakLigand, OakNucleotide

    public interface Exchangeable<FamilyType extends StructuralFamily>
    Exchangeable defines an entity that is exchangeable in terms of mapping another label or a set of other labels to that entity.

    This constitutes a surjective mapping of StructuralFamilys.

    By default an entity implementing Exchangeable is always exchangeable with itself.
